  "tips": [
    {
      "title": "The six modal verbs",
      "body": "Memorize all six: koennen (can), muessen (must), wollen (want), sollen (should), duerfen (may), moegen (like). They all send the main verb to the end as an infinitive."
    },
    {
      "title": "Word order golden rule",
      "body": "The conjugated verb is ALWAYS in position 2 in a main clause. Time-Manner-Place order for details: 'Ich fahre morgen mit dem Zug nach Berlin' (when, how, where)."
    },
    {
      "title": "Keep practicing after A1",
